ITEM 1 60 ADJ1=187 VAL2=1035
ITEM 2 554 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=292
ITEM 3 249 ADJ1=225 ADJ2=308 ADJ3=143
ITEM 4 249 ADJ1=259 ADJ2=308 ADJ3=143
ITEM 5 400 ADJ1=294 ADJ2=468
ITEM 6 249 ADJ1=468 ADJ2=308 ADJ3=143
ITEM 7 249 ADJ1=419 ADJ2=308 ADJ3=143
ITEM 8 249 ADJ1=248 ADJ2=308 ADJ3=143
ITEM 9 249 ADJ1=831 ADJ2=308 ADJ3=143
PUT 2 198 ADJ1=77 ADJ2=56 VAL2=1000
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The water in the basin appears to glow softly as you turn away, though as
you gaze at it once again the effect fades, leaving only pure, crystal clear
water. A flowery message is enscribed around the basin's rim.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
"Water, clear water, sweet essence of life.
 Cleanser of darkness, reflector of light.
 If truth do you see, then my answers confide...
 Partake of my substance, and welcome inside."
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
A fiery orange sun sets on the horizon over a world torn by a tremendous
cataclysm. The Gods have gathered on the crest of a mountain and formed
a circle, their concentration intense, as they attempt to restore life
to the shattered land.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
Amilor leads a mighty army of mortals against Siryx the Usurper,
fearlessly casting him from the heavens and restoring order to the world.
A small golden plaque is placed beneath the window.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
"Let it be known that I am eternally grateful to those who aided us
in our time of need. Forever, they will be the true sons and daughters
of Amilor, Lord of the Deep."
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 6
Standing side by side embracing one another, their hands joined over Andor,
Shemri and Amilor bless the entire world with their holy union.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 7
Maenar, Amilor's son, strides purposefully towards a monstrous
slumbering octopus unaware of the trap he enters. The final pane shows
Amilor, tears streaming down his cheeks, carrying Maenar's lifeless
form slowly into the waves.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 8
A great war rages upon a blood-soaked beach, Amilor's Knights locked in
mortal combat with Calumra's Minions. In the storming skies overhead
Amilor thrusts a trident formed from forked lightning into Calmura's
body, the tentacles of the Octopus demon coiled around him in a
death embrace.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 9
The enemy long vanquished, Amilor sits on a magnificent golden throne
encrusted with mother of pearl, sapphires and aquarmarines. He welcomes
his children home while a host of brilliantly colored fish and dolphins
pay court.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO 0
	DISBAND
	CLEARVERB
	IFITEM -1 OPEN
		IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
			ECHO PLAYER You proceed through the door, secure in the knowledge that Amilor welcomes you into his temple.
			ECHO OTHERS %N passes through the doorway.
			MOVE 592
			AFFECT 592
			ECHO OTHERS %N enters the courtyard.
			AFFECT 591
		ELSE
			ECHO PLAYER An unseen force prevents you from going through the doorway.
		ENDIF
	ELSE
		ECHO PLAYER The door is closed.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB TOUCH 2
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER You have already received a blessing from Amilor.
    ECHO OTHERS %N examines the bowl again.
  ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
     ECHO PLAYER You gently dip your fingers into the soothing waters and feel a sense of calm wash over you.
     ECHO OTHERS %N's face lights into a serene smile as %s dips %h fingers into the water.
     EQUAL FLAG1 1
   ENDIF
ENDIF
