NUMBER 1040
NAME Temple of Amilor Chapterhouse
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
Racks full of ornamental and fully functionable weapons spaced between
large suits of armor line the walls in this otherwise sparsely furnished
chamber. A large circular depression filled with sand dominates the center
of this room and is surrounded by an intricately carved railing of multi-
colored coral. The blue and white coral spirals up like frothing waves to
form an arch with steps leading down into the pit. Framed paintings of famous
Knights decorate the walls. A door leads to the Training Hall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 43
ITEM 0 350 ADJ1=29 VAL2=42
ITEM 3 60 ADJ1=69 VAL2=1041
ITEM 4 345
ITEM 5 345
ITEM 6 345
ITEM 7 345

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The door is heavily reinforced with settings for a steel rod. The symbol
of the Knights of Amilor is emblazoned upon it. The symbol is of a stylized
knight, armored in seashell plate, wielding a glowing trident as he rides
proudly upon a Merhorse as it pounds through the churning waves.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 4
A grinning Wrathe Inglorian stands fast against a quartet of snarling sharkhor
guards, lightning flickering from the blade of might in one hand, a half eaten
sharkhor tail in the other.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 5
A shadowy Don Wand slips from the obscuring mists of the Inner Sea to slide a
foot of cold steel into the back of a surprised sharkhor priest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 6
Tain Stormblade swings a blazing claidhmore in a fiery arc against a
monstrous squid creature, sending ichor-dripping tentacles flying in
every direction.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 7
Sirhad Nelikan smiles coldly, locked in a gaze with a stunned sharkhor shaman,
its body beginning to smolder and burst into flame.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1041
NAME Temple of Amilor Sand Pit
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
As you pass under the arch you emerge into a large circular pit filled with
sand. Racks hang from the surrounding railing, filled with various weapons.
This area is often used for demonstrations and friendly sparring, but it is
empty now, save for you and the grizzled old knight who looks up from
sharpening his greatsword to ask, "So, are ye come fer training then? I ha'nt
nt got all day." A stuffed sharkhor dummy rotates slowly around its pole.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 60 VAL2=1040
ITEM 1 1704 ADJ1=723
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
A remarkably lifelike sharkhor stares back at you with cold black eyes which
seem to dare you to attack it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
VARIABLE vyrnon
IFENTRY
	IFVAR vyrnon ! 1
		GENMON 247
		EQUAL vyrnon 1
	ENDIF
	IFVAR INTNUM3 = 210
		RANDOM dummy1 1 10 0
		IFVAR dummy1 = 1
			ECHO ALL Vyrnon smiles at Aban and says, "Hey there Aban, ye have anything to teach your old master yet?". Vyrnon then laughs, his respect for Aban deeply evident in his eyes.
		ENDIF
		IFVAR dummy1 = 2
			ECHO ALL Vyrnon takes a long appraising look at Aban, then pokes him in the stomach, saying, "Have a nice big breakfast, Aban?"
		ENDIF
		IFVAR dummy1 > 2
			ECHO ALL Vyrnon smiles and nods at Aban.
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB PUNCH 1
  ECHO PLAYER The sharkhor spins swiftly on its axis and deals a staggering blow to your side, knocking you to the sand.
  ECHO OTHERS The sharkhor spins swiftly on its axis and deals a staggering blow to %n's side, knocking %i to the sand.
  POSITION LAY
ENDIF
IFVERB GESTURE 1
  ECHO PLAYER The sharkhor's eyes glow a bright red and the spell you attempted on it is hurled back at you, forcing you into a kneeling position!
  ECHO OTHERS The sharkhor's eyes glow a bright red and the spell %n just attempted on it is hurled back at %i, forcing %i into a kneeling position!
  POSITION KNEEL
ENDIF
IFVERB CONCENTRATE 1
   ECHO PLAYER You gather mental energies to hurl at the sharkhor... suddenly your mind goes blank as the sharkhor seems to laugh at you and you fall unceremoniously on your tush!
   ECHO OTHERS %N gathers mental energies to hurl at the sharkhor... suddenly %N's eyes roll up into %h head and %s falls onto %h tush as the sharkhor seems to chuckle softly.
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
  IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
    ECHO PLAYER ... and recall that Sir Vyrnon likes to talk about Jasmine, Aban, Taliesin, Lelldorin, Raningeth, Mofusa, Leander, Winter, Diane, Don Wand, Clarissa, Wrathe, Jedico, Phelan, Tain, Sirhad, Shane, Krista, Korazon, Rysh, Ashan, Dania, Siryx, Khyron, his sword and service.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY aban?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon grins and beams, saying, "Fond of crushers is that one, and a good Preceptor."
ENDIF
IFSAY winter?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon smiles fondly and says, "That lass is a wiz with magic, and has been a devoted follower of the temple. Too bad she belongs to the Arcana still."
ENDIF
IFSAY lisanne?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon fondly says, "A sweet girl that is, I still feel for the lass since Jedico left."
ENDIF
IFSAY jedico?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon sighs and says, "A wondrous smith was Jedico. I miss 'im still."
ENDIF
IFSAY taliesin?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon rolls his eyes and says, "He's a strong knight, and good of heart, but his puns and usin' psionics ha' give me more'n one gray hair."
ENDIF
IFSAY raningeth?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon smiles softly, "A feisty priest is that little gnome, if overly fond of smelly potions. Ye be sure to see him if ye needs any."
ENDIF
IFSAY Jasmine?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon smiles fondly, "She's the High Priestess now, good choice if you ask me. She's gentle, and her heart is pure and filled with love for Amilor. But she can be a tough one when need be... just ask the Coven of Dalrah!"
ENDIF
IFSAY vyrnon?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon looks up from his sword, giving you a steely glance. "Ayup, that's me name, what do ye want?"
ENDIF
IFSAY sword?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon looks down at his sword, "I received this for me service to Amilor, 'twas a beautiful ceremony." Then his eyes grow misty for a moment, and he turns away, muttering something about sand swirling around.
ENDIF
IFSAY revenge?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon glares and growls, "Don't ye be saying the name of that Unborn One in this temple!" Vyrnon turns away, but not before you notice a look of profound sadness on his face.
ENDIF
IFSAY diane?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon chuckles and says, "Aye, Diane is one of the best and most devout knights we've seen, but a more stubborn one ye would be hard to find."
ENDIF
IFSAY leander?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon ponders, then says, "That knight is a strange one. He was kinda half demon at one time, but Tkovaeh, the Raven Knight, is gone now, and only Leander remains."
ENDIF
IFSAY lelldorin?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon grins, saying, "A fine follower of Amilor he is, and the Foresters are lucky to have his leadership."
ENDIF
IFSAY service?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon closes his eyes, sifting through his memories, "'Twas nigh on to thirty years ago..." Vyrnon stops for a moment and rubs a scar on his cheek, "...a force of Calumra's beasties attacked us as were praying on the beach. We were outnumbered."
ENDIF
IFSAY Clarissa?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon smiles a bit sadly, "Ahh, she was a fine high priestess! Such compassion, such fire!" Vyrnon sighs heavily before continuing, "She never wandered from His path. I miss Clarissa, I do..."
ENDIF
IFSAY Don_Wand?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon's eyes twinkle in fond rememberance. "Sir Don! He was one of the first knights. The first to help young ones, he was. Liked to think before he talked, too!" Vyrnon stops speaking and chuckles at some private remembrance.
ENDIF
IFSAY Wrathe?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon beams proudly, "She has been one of the finest warriors in Fayd as long as I can remember. Why, just think what her skills would be like without all that eating!"
ENDIF
IFSAY Phelan?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon scowls and spits, "Don't say that name in this holy place! You know, he once murdered Clarissa in this very temple! I heard his cold blood finally caught up with him." Vyrnon rubs his sword in barely contained anger...
ENDIF
IFSAY mofusa?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon says, "That drakin is a strong and faithful knight, but the lad needs to take better care of his weapons!"
ENDIF
IFSAY Sirhad?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon smiles, "I heard he made sheriff once. He's a steady fighter, been a devout follower of Amilor..." Vyrnon's eyes reflect his nostalgia, "Why, he fought alongside Sir Don!"
ENDIF
IFSAY Tain?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon says, "I rarely see Tain these days. Went to help the sheriff, Shane told me. You know, you can tell he misses Clarissa if you look into his eyes."
ENDIF
IFSAY Korazon?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon chuckles, "I remember thumping him square on his rump when he was a young one! Seems like yesterday! Ye know, he was Amilor's chosen Champion! He killed Syrix single-handedly! They do grow up..."
ENDIF
IFSAY Shane?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon says, "That boy from the Shartans was Amilor's Guardian. Now he's married to Krista and has those two little ones... the ones Amilor blessed with His own hands!"
ENDIF
IFSAY Krista?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon smiles gently, "She's always been a sweet one. And such a pure heart. Her and Shane will sweeten your coffee! And those little ones, Dania and Ashan! You know, she mothered the two Mer children-Gavyn and Serena-that repopulated the Mer race."
ENDIF
IFSAY Rysh?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon says, pride in his voice, "He's a drakin, if you haven't noticed. But as devout a follower as they come, and crafty, too. He destroyed the coven! Now that was no easy feat!"
ENDIF
IFSAY Ashan?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon beams with delight, "He's the little boy Krista and Shane had, almost lost that one when she was pregnant. Watch him! He's mighty quiet, but he's got a mind on him...", Vyrnon wipes his eyes, "You know, that boy flew right from the day he was born!"
ENDIF
IFSAY Dania?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon seems thoughtful for a moment, "Ahh, that little one has the talent to be one of the best swordsmen I ever taught--If she practices. I remember when she used to show everyone that little dragon birth-mark!"
ENDIF
IFSAY Siryx?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon scowls, "I thought we were rid of him forever, but he returned again with that same General! The knights had to go after him again!"
ENDIF
IFSAY Khyron?
  ECHO ALL Vyrnon sighs, "He's one of the best swordsmen I ever saw! Had no morals at all, though. He fought on Syrix' side twice, and I hope we never see him again! He took over Shane's body for a time... Thought we lost Shane there for awhile."
ENDIF

NUMBER 1037
NAME Temple of Amilor Priests' Study
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
Sandstone walls embedded with pieces of coral and seashells form this
octagonal chamber, worked cunningly to resemble underwater sculptures.
The effect is further enhanced by the soft blue light filtering in through
tinted skylights set high in the vaulted ceiling. An oddly shaped table
dominates the room, surrounded by comfortable leather chairs. Bookcases,
housing tomes and many scripts containing the knowledge needed by the
Priests, line the walls. You notice that some construction has begun
on the Priest's personal quarters, which will be accessed by doors
leading from this room.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 593
ITEM 2 350 ADJ1=310 VAL2=1038 VAL3=51
ITEM 3 91 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=69
ITEM 4 86 ADJ1=180
ITEM 5 1028
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 3
The table appears to be formed from pieces of pink, blue and white coral
arranged in patterns resembling fish and other underwater creatures.
The top is protected with a smooth sheet of glass.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 5
The shelves contain works on magic, the healing arts and a few other
pursuits. Each volume is beautifully covered in pale blue leather
with a seashell embossed on the front.
*DESCRIPTION_END
