NUMBER 42
NAME Temple of Amilor Training Hall
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
Arrayed around a large statue of Amilor are numerous spots where the
priests and acolytes of the temple are engaged in improving their skills.
Thick mats have been placed on the floor along the northern wall of the
chamber to help cushion the falls of warriors in training. In contrast,
the southern side of the chamber seems to be a place of more quiet study
as evidenced by the large number of temple members engaged in the lore of
magic and history. Two large doors, blue and white, lead off to the inner
sanctums of the temple and a blue marble arch leads back to the outer temple
rooms. Fastened to one wall is a board with temple messages posted on it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
