NUMBER 1038
NAME Temple of Amilor Laboratory
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
Rich earthy scents and other less definable odors assault your nostrils as you
enter this chamber. All around you bubbling pots, tubes, cauldrons and vials
are filled with liquids in a rainbow of color. Two acolytes look up from a
violently bubbling vat, startled at your entrance and whisper a harsh, "Shhh!"
Waters lap at the edge of a large pool in one corner of the room which is
meant to help contain any volatile accidents. Resting beside racks of finished
vials set out to cool is another vat, filled with glowing molten glass.
The statuette of a small gnome is being used as a paperweight to keep a stack
of alchemy notes from being scattered.
*DESCRIPTION_END
