NUMBER 1035
NAME Temple of Amilor Wedding Chapel
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
The entire room glows with the colors of the sea as muted shafts of light
stream through the blue tinted windows striking the polished abalone shell
walls. The rainbow-like pieces form the pattern of waves cresting on the
ocean as well as the swirling currents beneath them. Placed before an ornate
altar is a small arch made of ruffled coral, decorated with pastel colored
ribbons. Tall potted palms, placed on the sand colored marble floor, rustle
gently in the slightest breeze.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 591
